properties.areaDesc: Indian Wells Valley; Kern County Desert
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 7 at 8:14PM PST until January 8 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Hanford CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Sustained westerly winds 20 to 30 mph, with gusts around
50 mph.

* WHERE...Mainly below Kern County mountain passes.

* WHEN...From 1 AM PST tonight until 10 AM PST Wednesday morning.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Strong wind gusts may blow down tree limbs. A few power outages
are possible. Travel will be difficult, particularly for high
profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways affected include, but are not
limited to Highway 14, Highway 178 below Walker Pass, and
Highway 58 below Tehachapi Pass, including the town of Mojave.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: A WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM PST TONIGHT UNTIL 10 AM PST WEDNESDAY MORNING
